<div class="content_div">
<h2 class="content-heading"> What does a multimedia animator expert do?</h2>
<p class="text_content">A multimedia animator expert has a lot of different responsibilities which require various skill
    sets. While they are an essential part of the job, animating and drawing are not the only tasks Multimedia Animation
    Expertise is responsible for. A brief description is :</p><br>
<h3><strong>Draw</strong></h3>
<p class="text_content">Whether the draw start on paper and are later scanned into a computer for creation or animating
    digitally from the start, they form the inugrations of the actual animations used in multimedia. Multimedia
    Animation Expert often specialise in either 2D animations or 3D visual imagery, as the animation techniques are
    pretty different. </p><br>
<h3><strong>Animation</strong></h3>
<p class="text_content">Once the initial drawing is complete, the Multimedia Animation Expert set about animating it.
    For 2D projects, this requires drawing each mapping and animation frame to an individual keyframe in the animation
    software. The trick is to divide the animation into key poses and remove them first, then fill in the interim
    shelves so the animation runs fluidly and smoothly. </p><br>
<h3><strong>Storyboard</strong></h3>
<p class="text_content">Multimedia animation experts are frequently tasked with storyboarding, mapping visually out an
    animation sequence in a chains of sketches. They often receive scripts or even vague concepts from clients or
    directors and must use their creativity to transform these concepts into r animations concrete ideas . </p><br>
<h3><strong>Edit</strong></h3>
<p class="text_content"> you may be part of a large team of other animators, editors, writers, UX designers, and a
    director—or you could end up wearing several hats yourself as a multimedia animation expert. It is not uncommon for
    multimedia animation experts to help edit the final animations based on client and director feedback.</p><br>
<h3><strong>Brainstorm</strong></h3>
<p class="text_content">You will need to hone your creative chops as an animation designer because you will be expected
    to participate in brainstorming sessions to conceptualise ideas. This is often one of the most enjoyable parts of
    the job for many people, but it could hamper your growth and job satisfaction if you need more creative skills. </p>
<br>
<h3><strong>Conceptual</strong></h3>
<p class="text_content">Along with contributing ideas, animation designers create quick sketches based on concepts
    developed during the sessions. If you are a perfectionist, you may need to manage your expectations for how long you
    can spend on them. </p><br>
</div>
